# Man page sync

When changing flags, config, or version, update **`contrib/man/man1/pgwd.1`** so `man pgwd` stays accurate.

## When to update

| Change | Action in pgwd.1 |
|--------|------------------|
| **New flag** | Add `.TP` block in OPTIONS with CLI name, env var, and brief description |
| **Removed/deprecated flag** | Remove or mark deprecated in OPTIONS |
| **Flag description change** | Update the corresponding `.TP` block |
| **VERSION bump** | Update `.TH PGWD 1` line: date and version (e.g. `"2026-03-13" "pgwd v0.5.0"`) |
| **New example** | Add to EXAMPLES section |

## Format reference

```troff
.TP
.BR \-flag\-name " \fIarg\fR"
Description. Env: PGWD_FLAG_NAME.
```

## Checklist before release

- [ ] All flags in `main.go` / `config.go` are documented in pgwd.1 OPTIONS
- [ ] `.TH` line has current date and version
- [ ] EXAMPLES reflect current usage (e.g. -kube-loki if applicable)

## Verify

```bash
MANPATH="$(pwd)/contrib/man:$(man -w)" man pgwd
```
